        a workplace pension you paid into, or both.</p>

      <p>There are different ways you can take the money from your pension
        pot.</p>

      <p>You can:</p>

      <ul>
        <li>take a tax-free lump sum from your pot</li>
        <li>take your whole pot as cash</li>
        <li>keep your pot invested while taking money from it (drawdown)</li>
        <li>buy a regular income (annuity)</li>
      </ul>

      <p>You can use a mixture of all 4 if you want.</p>

